Package com.karmant.syn

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    SourceDescriptor
    Source code (input) descriptor.
    TokenStream
    Token stream interface.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractToken
    Used by SynBinder to represent a pair of a text position and a value of a token of a particular type.
    ArrayNode
    Array node.
    DoubleToken
    Token value of type double.
    FileSourceDescriptor
    Source descriptor representing a File.
    FloatToken
    Token value of type float.
    IntToken
    Token value of type int.
    LongToken
    Token value of type long.
    ObjectNode
    Object node.
    StringSourceDescriptor
    Source descriptor representing an arbitrary String.
    StringToken
    Token value of type String.
    SynBinder<T>
    Binder - an add-on to SynParser that maps nonterminals and grammar attributes to client-supplied Java classes and fields, correspondingly.
    SynNode
    Abstract Syntax Tree (AST) node.
    SynParser
    A parser for a particular grammar.
    SynResult
    The result returned by a SynParser.
    TerminalNode
    Terminal node - a node that does not contain child nodes.
    TextPos
    A position in an input text.
    TokenDescriptor
    Token descriptor.
    ValueNode
    A terminal node that has an associated value, like an identifier or an integer number.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    SynValueType
    The type of a value associated with a value node.
    TokenType
    Token type.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    SynAmbiguityException
    Thrown by SynParser if a grammar ambiguity is detected, but only if the parser is configured to fail on an ambiguity.
    SynBinderException
    Thrown to indicate a SynBinder-related error: a grammar does not meet the Binder limitations or Java classes are not appropriate.
    SynException
    Common superclass for all SYN exception types.
    SynGrammarException
    Thrown if there is a semantical error in the grammar passed to a SynParser.
    SynLexicalException
    Signals an error in lexical analysis.
    SynSyntaxException
    Thrown to indicate a syntax error - a situation when the input does not match the grammar.
    SynTextException
    Text exception - an exception associated with a position in the input.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    SynField
    Indicates that a field has to be bound to a value of a grammar attribute.
    SynInit
    Indicates that a method is an initialization method, meaning that it has to be called by SynBinder after each initialization of each object.
    SynLookup
    Indicates that an object or a set of objects instantiated by SynBinder have to be bound to the annotated field, if that objects satisfy the specified filter.
